---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { galleries } from '../data/galleries';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Generative Art Pipelines">
  <article class="max-w-[65ch] mx-auto px-6 py-20 stagger-in">

    <!-- 1. Hero -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="font-display italic text-text" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);">
        What is this?
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        A living gallery of algorithmic 2D art — each piece generated by a self-contained
        pipeline, running live in your browser.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. The Idea -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display italic text-3xl text-text mb-6">The Idea</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Generative art sits at the intersection of code and aesthetics — algorithms
          that produce visual beauty not through pixel-perfect design, but through
          emergent behavior. A few lines of math can produce infinite visual variation.
        </p>
        <p>
          We chose p5.js because it strips away the ceremony of graphics programming
          and lets the algorithm speak. Each sketch is a conversation between parameters
          and chaos, between intention and surprise.
        </p>
        <p>
          The pipeline architecture means every piece is self-contained: a single file
          that defines its parameters, its setup logic, and its draw loop. No shared
          mutable state, no hidden dependencies. Drop a file in, and it works.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. How Pipelines Work -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display italic text-3xl text-text mb-6">How Pipelines Work</h2>
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded p-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <pre class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted leading-relaxed"><code>{`Pipeline Interface
├── id          → unique kebab-case identifier
├── name        → display name
├── theme       → which gallery it belongs to
├── description → 1-2 sentence summary
├── tags[]      → searchable keywords
├── params{}    → parameter schema (range, color, boolean, select)
│
├── setup(p5, params, canvas)
│   └── called once → returns mutable state
│
├── draw(p5, params, state, frame)
│   └── called every frame → renders the art
│
├── onParamChange?(p5, params, state)
│   └── called when user tweaks a parameter
│
└── destroy?(state)
    └── cleanup on unmount`}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. The Themes -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display italic text-3xl text-text mb-6">The Themes</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        {galleries.sort((a, b) => a.order - b.order).map(theme => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div
              class="w-4 h-4 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0"
              style={`background: ${theme.accentColor}`}
            ></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display italic text-xl text-text">{theme.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-1">{theme.description}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. Tech Stack -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display italic text-3xl text-text mb-6">Tech Stack</h2>
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded overflow-hidden">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 label">Framework</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text">Astro</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 label">Art Runtime</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text">p5.js</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 label">Styling</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text">Tailwind CSS</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 label">Deployment</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text">Vercel</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Add a Pipeline -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display italic text-3xl text-text mb-6">Add a Pipeline</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-text-muted leading-relaxed list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>Create file at <code class="text-accent text-xs">src/pipelines/[theme]/[kebab-name].ts</code></li>
        <li>Implement the <code class="text-accent text-xs">Pipeline</code> interface from <code class="text-accent text-xs">src/pipelines/_types.ts</code></li>
        <li>Export it as a named const</li>
        <li>Create page at <code class="text-accent text-xs">src/pages/gallery/[theme]/[kebab-name].astro</code></li>
        <li>Add a card to the theme's <code class="text-accent text-xs">index.astro</code> gallery page</li>
        <li>Drop a preview PNG at <code class="text-accent text-xs">public/previews/[pipeline-id].png</code></li>
        <li>Done — Vercel deploys automatically on push</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-text-muted mt-4 text-sm">
        Or use the CLI: <code class="text-accent text-xs">pnpm generate --name "my-piece" --theme organic</code>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. GitHub -->
    <section class="text-center">
      <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn inline-flex">
        View on GitHub
      </a>
    </section>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
